The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Karat on harmony panel

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Prakash Karat

 New Delhi, Aug. 25: CPM general secretary Prakash Karat has been nominated to the reconstituted National Integration Council, headed by Prime Minister Manmohan Singh.

 Karat joins the council in the category of leaders of national political parties, the home ministry spokesman said.

 CII president Y.C. Deveshwar has also been included, replacing Sunil Kant Munjal. In the womens representative category, the general secretary of the National Federation of Indian Women, Annie Raja, replaces Sehba Farooqui. Mohammed Afzal joins under the head eminent public figures.

 The council and its committees come under the home ministry. They discuss problems on the communal front and try to arrive at a consensus. The previous council was constituted in February this year.




